President Muhammadu Buhari has sent a message of condolence to the leader of the Tijjaniyya Movement, Sheikh Dahiru Usman Bauchi over the death of his wife, Aisha Usman Bauchi. In his reaction after receiving the news of the death, President Buhari said, “it is with a heavy heart and grief that I received the news of the death of your devoted wife, Hajiya Aisha.” He said the late Aisha “was an exemplary woman and a devoted mother whose virtues should be a fountain of inspiration to all members of the family.” The President, while expressing his sympathy to the family, prayed to God to forgive the soul of the deceased and grant her eternal bliss in paradise Buhari’s condolence message was made available to DAILY POST on Tuesday by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu.